    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, the only easy way to get a mapping with its callback is using `maparg()` which is not lua.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI'm basically suggesting to make `vim.keymap.get` to a wrapper around `maparg()` (or `nvim_get_keymap`)\r\nYou can use it as if it was like `maparg()`:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal map=vim.keymap.get('i','K',{})\r\nif map.lhsraw==':w\\rK' then\r\n  --..\r\nend\r\n```\r\nI'm also suggesting an option to have an opt `return_format='map'` which would return the same table as before but extended with such values that unpack it would give the right arguments to `vim.keymap.set` to redefine the map.\r\n```lua\r\nlocal map=vim.keymap.get('i','K',{return_format='map'})\r\n--...\r\nvim.keymap.set(unpack(map))\r\n```",
