            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Found a problem with `maparg()`: it only returns the current buffers keymap.\r\nThis means that using `maparg` you can't:\r\n1. Get keymaps from non-current buffers\r\n2. Get a global keymap if buffer has a buffer-local keymap\r\nAnd requires the usage of `nvim_get_keymap` with filtering.\r\nMy biggest problem here is not that you need to do extra but that it is really easy to accidentally create a bug if you don't know the second point.\r\nThou I don't know if this is enough to create a totally new API function, probably should just add to `nvim_get_keymap` documentation about when not to use `maparg()`.",
            "created_at": "2023-07-14T04:45:20Z",
